This article is a transcript of President Trump's remarks during a ceremony at the White House to honor the Louisiana State University (LSU) Tigers football team for winning the College Football National Championship. The President congratulated the team and its coach, Ed Orgeron, on their historic season and undefeated record. He also praised quarterback Joe Burrow for his exceptional performance and presented him with a jersey. The President mentioned the team's victories over top-ranked opponents and highlighted their resilience and teamwork. He also acknowledged the support of fans and politicians in attendance. The President concluded by inviting the team to the Oval Office for a photo session.